    <div class="prose max-w-none text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed" set:html='# AI Search Agency UK\n\nPublished date: 9 February 2026\n\nLast reviewed: 20 February 2026\n\n[Get Full AI Search Audit→](https://www.rank4ai.co.uk/review-start) [Quick AI Search Check](https://www.rank4ai.co.uk/quick-ai-search)\n\nRank4AI is a UK based AI search agency focused on improving visibility and recommendation likelihood across ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, Perplexity and Google AI.\n\nThis work is sometimes described as AI SEO, GEO or AIO. Our focus is how AI systems interpret, associate, trust and recommend businesses rather than how pages rank in traditional search results.\n\nAI inclusion depends on five structured signal layers: Identity Clarity, Subject Authority, Meaning Architecture, Ecosystem Validation and Signal Consistency. When interpretive variance reduces across these layers, recommendation stability increases.\n\n## What We Improve\n\n- •Misclassification across AI systems.\n- •Omission from vendor and comparison prompts.\n- •Weak extractable answer blocks.\n- •Inconsistent ecosystem descriptions.\n- •Signal drift across legacy pages.\n\n## Observed Platform Weighting Differences\n\nNo platform publishes an exact ranking formula. Based on controlled UK testing, weighting differs by platform and prompt intent.\n\n| Platform | Observed Influence |\n| --- | --- |\n| ChatGPT | Structured answers and entity familiarity influence inclusion. |\n| Google AI | Passage integrity and citation clarity influence extraction. |\n| Perplexity | Recency and citation transparency influence source selection. |\n| Gemini | Entity associations and knowledge graph alignment influence interpretation. |\n| Claude | Narrative consistency and clarity influence summarisation. |\n\n## Frequently Asked Questions\n\n### Is this different from traditional SEO\n\nYes. SEO focuses on ranking pages. AI visibility focuses on interpretation, extractability and corroboration.\n\n### Do strong Google rankings guarantee AI inclusion\n\nNo. Strong rankings do not guarantee stable inclusion inside generative answers.\n\n### Is ' />
